{
  "text": "Mitigating adversarial inputs remains an open problem, even in the image-domain. A complicating factor in detecting the AdEx attacks include variations due to the physical world. Visual adversarial perturbations and their robustness given different backgrounds, lighting, and camera resolutions is discussed in [CITATION_1] . The diversity of RF communications, radar, and spectrum sensing systems, and complex propagation channels makes this problem in the RF domain even more complex and unique. The effect of the channel (or interference) which is mitigated in well-designed communications receivers will persist at the DL classifier, thus changing the classification for both legitimate inputs and AdExs. Although we reflect on these issues, the proper consideration and modeling of the both hardware and the RF channel are outside the scope of this paper.",
